#Case Study — OONP Approval (Pathway 1 + 2)

> This documents the real timeline of applying for OONP approval 
> under an existing ReOC. Company details are anonymised.
>
> **Operator:** Small commercial operator, Sydney metro area  
> **ReOC category:** Sub-250g, 250-2kg, Sub-25kg multirotor  
> **Pathways sought:** P1 (controlled environment) + P2 (energy-based)  
> **Operation types:** Building wash + aerial filming

---

##Timeline

| Date | Action | Notes |
|------|--------|-------|
| 09 April 2026 | Going through documents as listed in OONP/01-overview-and-pathways |
| 11 April 2026 | Going through documents as listed in OONP/01-overview-and-pathways and creating the guide |

Expected work to be done:
- Gap analysis of current ReOC | Map current manual against TMI 2024-01 requirements
- Energy calculations completed | KE calcs for RPA across all flight modes/weights/speeds
- Draft the ConOps | 2-page standalone document for CASA
- Draft/Update Ops manual OONP section | Section 2.4.6.3 populated with full procedures
- Draft/Update Consent forms | Express written (P1) + informed consent (P2) + occupant notification
- Internal review and CRP sign-off | Consistency check
- Submission to CASA | RPAS Multi-Purpose Form + all supporting docs |

Dates be noted down:
- CASA acknowledged receipt
- Feedbacks received (if any) | What they asked for, what we changed
- CRP interview / Q&A (if required)
- Approval granted | Conditions and limitations noted


